Then record the amount to the user's account.

totalSupply().details: Returns the amount of tokens in existence.

addWorker(address).notice: Add new worker to the system. Returns a boolean value indicating whether the operation succeeded. Emits a {AddWorker} event.

appeal().notice: When the user's withdrawn account has money, and the block height minus withdrawn height greater than 6, the user can submit an appeal. Emits an {Appeal} event.

appealRefund(address).notice: When a user didn't receive the amount after he withdrew, he can submit an appeal. Admin call this function to refund. Emits a {AdminAppealRefund} event.

balanceOf(address).notice: Returns the amount of balance owned by `account`.

changeOwner(address).notice: Change the owner of the contract. If the address is a contract, the contract should be IAdmin.

deposit().notice: User deposit money to the system, system select a worker then send the money to it. Then record the amount to the user's account. If the user's withdrawn account has money, he can't deposit. Emits a {Deposit} event.

getAppealedBalance(address).notice: Returns the amount of appealed balance owned by `account`.

getInterest(address).notice: Returns the amount of interest owned by `account`.

getWithdrawnBalance(address).notice: Returns the amount of withdrawn balance owned by `account`.

isWorker(address).notice: Check an address whether the worker.

refund(address).notice: Worker refund money to user when user submit withdraw request. Emits a {RefundMoney} event.

refundToOwner().notice: This operation will be executed when someone do a wrong operate, e.g., send CPC directly to the contract. Use this function to refund CPC to the owner.

removeWorker(address).notice: Remove a existed worker from system. Returns a boolean value indicating whether the operation succeeded. Emits a {RemoveWorker} event.

setTxLowerLimit(uint256).notice: Set the lower limit per tx.

setTxUpperLimit(uint256).notice: Set the upper limit per tx.

setUserBalanceLimit(uint256).notice: Set the upper limit of user's balance.

setWithdrawFee(uint256).notice: Set the fee when withdraw money. The unit of the param is 1/10000. And the param should greater than 0 and less than 100 (0 - 1%)

setWithdrawnUpperLimit(uint256).notice: Set the upper limit when withdraw

setWorkerBalanceLimit(uint256).notice: Set the upper limit of worker's balance.

statsInterest(uint256).notice: Stats the interest that all workers earned yesterday and distributed by the ratio of balance of all addresses. Returns a boolean value indicating whether the operation succeeded. Emits a {StatsInterest} event.

transfer(address,uint256).notice: Moves `amount` tokens from the caller's account to `recipient`. Returns a boolean value indicating whether the operation succeeded.     * Emits a {Transfer} event.

withdraw(uint256).notice: User withdraw money. The system select a worker and emit a Event to notify it. Move the withdrawn money to the withdrawn account, wait until the worker refund. If the user's appeal account has money, he can't withdraw. Emits a {Withdraw} event.

workerBalanceOf(address).notice: Returns the amount of balance owned by `account`.
